court: IN THE HIGH COURT OF PUNJAB & HARYANA AT CHANDIGARH CWP No.10257 of 1994 Date of decision:17.05.2012 Inspector Shyam Singh RR/76 .....Petitioner Versus State of Haryana & others .....Respondents CORAM : HON'BLE MR.JUSTICE G.S.SANDHAWALIA Present: None for the petitioner, Ms.Aakanksha Sawhney, DAG, Haryana. G.S.Sandhawalia J. (Oral) . Challenge in the writ petition is to the order dated 15.07.1995 (Annexure P-4) whereby the petitioner's seniority was re-fixed. . The case was ordered to be heard along with CWP No.15474 of . While issuing notice of motion, a Division Bench of this Court ordered status quo and the interim order was continued. The case was admitted on 19.09.1996. The said case, i.e., CWP No.15474 of 1994 has been disposed of as having been rendered infructuous and also for non- prosecution. Accordingly, the present writ petition is also disposed of as having been rendered infructuous by sheer efflux of time and also for non-prosecution. .05.2012 (G.S.Sandhawalia) sailesh JUDGE
